Follow these steps:-

1.Install Node.js on your system using 'sudo apt-get install nodejs' and Node package manager using 'sudo apt-get install npm' and check whether installed by typing 'node -v' and 'npm -v'.
2.In the root directory, type the command 'npm i slack'.
3.Navigate to the slack folder and type 'npm install' to install all the dependencies.
4.Create a file called .env in the root with the following:
SLACK_TOKEN=xxxx
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xxxx
SLACK_CLIENT_ID=xxxx
SLACK_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxx
CHANNEL_NAME='<YOUR CHANNEL NAME>'
For SLACK_TOKEN: access https://api.slack.com/custom-integrations/legacy-tokens
For SLACK_BOT_TOKEN:-access https://my.slack.com/services/new/bot
                    -create a new bot and get its token(starts with xoxb)                     
For SLACK_CLIENT_ID and SLACK_CLIENT_SECRET:- Register an app through https://api.slack.com/apps
         - Click on "Create new app" and get the Client id and Client secret after creating.
5.Type 'npm start' to run the code
6.Open the browser to access http://localhost:3000
7.The table will be displayed.
